    <h2></h2>
    <p class="first-paragraph">
      <b>The Spiral Draft</b> is not just a story—it's a reflection folded into the ink. In the world of fragmented narratives and forgotten characters, the line between creator and creation blurs into a haunting spiral. The story builds like a whisper, drawing you closer to the margins of fiction, until you realize you're not just reading it. You’re part of it.
    </p>
    <p>
      This world exists not only in words, but in pauses, redactions, drafts that never saw light. The character named Nox was believed to be a ghostwriter—but who was truly writing whom? And in Aranya’s arrival, we see the first ripple of rebellion: the reader becoming a writer, the silence turning into voice.
    </p>
    <p>
      As each chapter unfolds, the draft reshapes itself. What you thought was certain becomes ephemeral. A name reappears. A loop closes. And the story... writes back.
    </p>
